  "spellClass": "Clérigo",
  "combatNotes": "COMBOS & TACTICS (Cleric 1 — Grave Domain):\n• Circle of Mortality: when healing a creature at 0 HP, all healing dice roll maximum — always use Healing Word (bonus action) to bring allies up.\n• Healing Word vs Cure Wounds: Healing Word is bonus action range — use it 99% of the time. Save Cure Wounds for when you need max healing.\n• Path to the Grave (Channel Divinity): curse a target → it has vulnerability to ALL damage until end of your next turn. Combo: curse → ally attacks → massive damage.\n• Bane (concentration): up to 3 enemies subtract 1d4 from attacks and saves — excellent opener in any fight.\n• Inflict Wounds (melee): 3d10 necrotic on a hit — highest single-target damage at this level if you can close distance.\n• Sacred Flame (cantrip): DEX save, ignores cover — use on targets behind obstacles.\n• Eyes of the Grave: free undead detection in 60ft — always use before exploring new rooms.\n• Turn Undead / Expunge Undead: reaction panic button vs undead groups.\n• Tip: open with Bane, then Path to the Grave + ally burst. Keep Healing Word in reserve every round. Stay in the back — you're the party's only healer.",
